== Mosquito flight ==

Forgive my ignorance, but I got the impression years ago the Bohr was in fact quite reluctant to be spirited to the UK to aid British/Allied research efforts during the war. In fact, I thought that he had to be practically forced into the Mosquito. Can anyone enlighten on this, and if so, can it be included in the article? Thanks.  <small><span class="autosigned">—&nbsp;Preceding [[Wikipedia:Signatures|unsigned]] comment added by [[User:Isoruku|Isoruku]] ([[User talk:Isoruku|talk]] • [[Special:Contributions/Isoruku|contribs]]) 18:26, 22 April 2016 (UTC)</span></small><!-- Template:Unsigned --> <!--Autosigned by SineBot-->
:Bohr was aware that the British government wanted him to come to Britain at once. He delayed a few days in order to make his personal appeal to the King Gustav V to allow Jewish refugees to stay. [[User:Hawkeye7|Hawkeye7]] ([[User talk:Hawkeye7|talk]]) 21:52, 22 April 2016 (UTC)

::Just how exactly were they supposed to 'force' him into the Mosquito when they were at a [[Stockholm Bromma Airport|civil airport in a neutral country]] where all he had to do was shout for help to anyone nearby.  <small class="autosigned">—&nbsp;Preceding [[Wikipedia:Signatures|unsigned]] comment added by [[Special:Contributions/95.149.172.200|95.149.172.200]] ([[User talk:95.149.172.200|talk]]) 10:29, 14 May 2016 (UTC)</small><!-- Template:Unsigned IP --> <!--Autosigned by SineBot-->
:::He wasn't forced; he went voluntarily. [[User:Hawkeye7|Hawkeye7]] ([[User talk:Hawkeye7|talk]]) 20:33, 14 May 2016 (UTC)
